        <scopecontent>The series consists of photographs (mainly copyprints) and photocopies of photographs. The images document the "Deer Mission" organized by the Office of Strategic Services and led by Allison Thomas in the Kim Long area of Vietnam in 1945. The photographs show OSS members parachuting into the region, the base camp near Kim Long, the training of guerilla forces, and their interactions with Ho Chi Minh and Vo Nguyen Giap.</scopecontent>
